.TH SFE 1
.SH NAME
sfe \- SSH-friendly terminal C code editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sfe
[\fIfile\fR]
.br
.B sfe
[\fB--version\fR|\fB-v\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sfe
is a lightweight terminal editor for SSH sessions. It keeps common Vim-style
save and quit commands while adding C syntax highlighting, completions,
local header scanning, line numbers, smart indentation, undo/redo, and simple
function signature help.
.PP
Version 0.4.2 adds project file workflow commands: a toggleable project tree
pane, fuzzy project open, recent files, build/run helpers, compiler error
parsing, and navigation across both editor diagnostics and build diagnostics.
.PP
Version 0.4.3 publishes amd64 and arm64 Debian packages with a private Python
runtime inside each package, so installing the downloaded .deb does not require
apt to fetch Python or other runtime dependencies.
.PP
Version 0.4.4 builds release runtimes on Ubuntu 22.04 and rejects bundled
binaries that require GLIBC symbols newer than 2.35, improving compatibility
with Ubuntu 22.04 hosts.
.PP
Version 0.4.5 defers local header, project symbol, and project file tree scans
until completion, definition jump, tree, or fuzzy-open commands need them. This
makes opening a file in a large project faster while keeping project features
available on demand.
.PP
Version 0.4.6 makes the launcher prefer /usr/bin/python3 with bytecode writes
and Python site initialization disabled for faster startup, while keeping the
bundled Python runtime as an automatic fallback when system Python or curses is
unavailable.
.PP
Version 0.4.9 handles --version and -v directly in the launcher and ships
precompiled editor bytecode, reducing Python import and compile work before the
editor screen opens.
.PP
Version 0.5.0 adds a multi-buffer workspace. Opening files from :e, :open,
:files, Ctrl-P, or the project tree switches to an existing buffer or creates a
new buffer while keeping unsaved edits, cursor position, scroll position, undo
history, and diagnostics in other buffers.
.PP
Version 0.5.1 adds configurable command shortcuts with :bind and makes Ctrl-W
open the project tree when it is currently closed.
.PP
Version 0.5.2 allows :bind command shortcuts to use Ctrl-Left, Ctrl-Right,
Ctrl-Up, and Ctrl-Down, including terminal-specific curses key codes such as
561 for Ctrl-Right.
.PP
Version 0.5.3 uses terminal key names to distinguish real Ctrl-arrow keys,
including 546 for Ctrl-Left on xterm-compatible terminals, and rejects
shortcuts that conflict with terminal, shell/readline, tmux/screen, Vim, or
built-in SFE behavior.
.PP
Opening binary files, files containing NUL bytes, or files that are not valid
UTF-8 shows an unsupported-file dialog instead of crashing the terminal UI.
.PP
Version 0.5.4 keeps the current buffer unchanged when unsupported files are
opened from startup, :e, :files, or the project tree.
.PP
Version 0.5.5 refreshes the visible project tree after :make, accepts : while
the project tree has focus, and opens a Run Output list when :run prints stdout
or stderr.
.PP
Version 0.5.6 opens Build Errors automatically when :make fails, lets r rerun
from the Run Output list, and adds :N, :pwd, and :!cmd workflow commands.
.PP
Version 0.5.7 adds gg, G, Ctrl-D, and Ctrl-U movement, shows an Unsaved Buffers
list when :q or quit shortcuts find modified buffers, marks DIRTY and RO files
in the status line, and reports elapsed time for :make and :run.
.PP
Version 0.6.0 adds dd, yy, p, dw, cw, Ctrl-F, and Ctrl-B editing/navigation,
plus :%s/old/new/g substitution and :wqa save-all quit. Ctrl-F now scrolls down
a full screen; use / for search.
.PP
Version 0.7.0 makes Ctrl-] prefer include jumps on #include lines, adds
:outline as a jumpable current-file symbol list, keeps :symbols compatible, and
adds conservative C diagnostics for duplicate local variables, obviously unused
locals, orphan else, duplicate case labels, and duplicate default labels.
.PP
Version 0.8.0 makes :files and Ctrl-P filterable, adds quick character locate
in the project tree, preserves tree selection across refreshes, shows fast git
branch status when available, and reuses cached project file scans across the
file picker, project tree, and fuzzy open.
.PP
When auto pairing is enabled, typing {, (, [, " or ' inserts the matching
right side as a dim placeholder. Pressing Enter between an automatic {} pair
keeps the closing brace aligned with the opening brace, and typing the matching
right side again jumps over the placeholder instead of inserting a duplicate.
.PP
Insert-mode Backspace removes an empty pair such as {} in one step and removes
one indentation level on otherwise empty indentation. Typing } on an indented
blank line aligns it with the containing block.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --version, -v
Print the installed sfe version and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B i
Enter Insert mode.
.TP
.B Esc
Return to Normal mode.
.TP
.B :w
Save the current file.
.TP
.B :q
Quit if there are no unsaved changes. If any buffer is modified, show the
Unsaved Buffers list instead of exiting.
.TP
.B :q!
Quit without saving changes.
.TP
.B :wq
Save and quit.
.TP
.B :wqa
Save all named modified buffers and quit. If a modified [No Name] buffer exists,
show Unsaved Buffers and do not exit.
.TP
.B u
Undo the last edit in Normal mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl-R
Redo the last undone edit in Normal mode.
.TP
.B n
Repeat the last search forward.
.TP
.B N
Repeat the last search backward.
.TP
.B gg
Jump to the beginning of the file.
.TP
.B G
Jump to the end of the file.
.TP
.B Ctrl-D, Ctrl-U
Move down or up by half a screen.
.TP
.B Ctrl-F, Ctrl-B
Move down or up by a full screen.
.TP
.B dd
Delete the current line and copy it to the line clipboard.
.TP
.B yy
Copy the current line to the line clipboard.
.TP
.B p
Paste the copied/deleted line below the current line.
.TP
.B dw
Delete forward to the next word boundary.
.TP
.B cw
Delete forward to the next word boundary and enter Insert mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl-]
Jump to the definition of the symbol under the cursor. On #include lines, jump
to a local include when it can be found in the current directory or project root;
system includes report the header name without opening a guessed path.
.TP
.B Ctrl-O
Jump back after a definition jump.
.TP
.B Ctrl-N
Move to the next editor diagnostic or build error.
.TP
.B Ctrl-P
Open the project file list in Normal or Insert mode.
.TP
.B :tree
Toggle the left project tree pane.
.TP
.B :tree open, :tree close
Explicitly open or close the project tree pane.
.TP
.B Ctrl-W
Open the project tree pane when it is closed. When the tree is already open,
switch focus between the project tree pane and the editor window.
.TP
.B Enter
In the project tree, expand or collapse the selected directory, or open the
selected file in the editor window as a buffer.
.TP
.B q, Esc
Close the project tree pane when it has focus.
.TP
.B :open PATTERN
Fuzzy-open the best matching project file.
.TP
.B :files
Show project files with a live filter. Type to filter, Backspace to edit the
filter, Enter to open or switch to the selected buffer, and Esc to close.
.TP
.B :recent
Show recently opened project files.
.TP
.B :buffers
Show open buffers. The current buffer is marked with %, and modified buffers are
marked with +.
.TP
.B :bn, :bnext
Switch to the next buffer, wrapping at the end.
.TP
.B :bp, :bprevious
Switch to the previous buffer, wrapping at the beginning.
.TP
.B :bd, :bdelete
Delete the current buffer if it has no unsaved changes. Deleting the last clean
buffer creates a new empty [No Name] buffer.
.TP
.B :bind COMMAND
Prompt for a shortcut key and bind it to COMMAND. Supported commands are
.B buffers,
.B bn,
.B bp,
.B bd,
.B files,
and
.B tree.
The captured shortcut is shown in the status line and saved to
.B ~/.config/sfe/config.json.
SFE rejects shortcuts that commonly conflict with terminal, shell/readline,
tmux/screen, Vim, or built-in SFE behavior, and shows the conflict reason in
the status line. Prefer low-conflict shortcuts such as F3 through F9 or
Ctrl-arrow keys.
.TP
.B :make
Run the configured build command, or use make / gcc fallback. Failed builds open
the Build Errors list automatically. The status line reports elapsed time.
.TP
.B :run
Run the configured run command or the last detected build output. In Run Output,
press r to rerun the same command. The status line reports elapsed time.
.TP
.B :errors
Show compiler errors and warnings captured by :make.
.TP
.B :N
Move to line N, for example :42.
.TP
.B :goto N
Move to line N.
.TP
.B :pwd
Show the current project root or working directory in the status line.
.TP
.B :!cmd
Run cmd in the project root and show stdout and stderr in a list.
.TP
.B :%s/old/new/g
Replace all literal matches of old with new in the current buffer.
.TP
.B :outline
Show current-file symbols by kind. Press Enter on a selected symbol to jump to
that line.
.TP
.B :symbols
Alias for :outline.
.TP
.B :diag
Show lightweight C diagnostics.
.TP
.B :help
Show in-editor help.
.TP
.B :e FILE
Open FILE in a buffer. If FILE is already open, switch to its existing buffer.
.TP
.B :w FILE
Save the current buffer as FILE.
.TP
.B :set auto_pair on|off
Enable or disable automatic paired character insertion.
.TP
.B :set completion_key KEY
Set the manual completion trigger.
.TP
.B :set number on|off
Show or hide line numbers.
.SH COMPLETION AND DIAGNOSTICS
Completions include C keywords, snippets, standard library symbols, current
file identifiers, local headers, local header symbols, and project symbols from
.B .c
and
.B .h
files under the current file directory. Snippets include
.B main,
.B for,
.B if,
and
.B switch.
.PP
Diagnostics report unmatched brackets, unterminated strings, duplicate includes,
and simple missing semicolons. The status line shows the current diagnostic
count, buffer position, DIRTY marker for modified buffers, and RO marker for
read-only files.
.SH CONFIGURATION
User configuration is read from
.B ~/.config/sfe/config.json
and overrides the system defaults in
.B /etc/sfe/config.json.
.PP
Supported keys include
.B auto_pair,
.B completion_key,
.B indent_width,
.B show_line_numbers,
.B scan_local_headers,
.B signature_help,
.B build_command,
.B run_command,
.B project_root_markers,
.B recent_files_limit,
and
.B keybindings.
.PP
.B keybindings
maps shortcut names such as
.B f3,
.B ctrl+right,
or other accepted low-conflict shortcuts
to commands such as
.B bn,
.B bp,
.B buffers,
.B bd,
.B files,
or
.B tree.
.PP
If
.B build_command
is empty,
.B :make
uses
.B make
when a Makefile exists. For a current C source file, it falls back to
.B gcc <file> -o <stem>.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/sfe/config.json
System default configuration.
.TP
.B ~/.config/sfe/config.json
User configuration.
.SH UPGRADE
Run
.B sfe-upgrade
to download and install the latest GitHub release package. The helper sends
GitHub API headers and a user agent to work better behind proxies and rate
limit filters.
